com.cognos.CAM_AAA.authentication

Interface IAuthenticationListener


  • public interface IAuthenticationListener
    Defines the interface to use for implementing an IBM Cognos authentication listener.

    • Method Detail

      • logon

        void logon(java.lang.String passportID,
           java.lang.String namespaceID,
           java.lang.String userID,
           IBiBusHeader theBiBusHeader)
        Invoked after a successful logon has occured. If a user logs on to multiple namespaces there will be a logon event for each namespace and the passportID will remain the same.
        Parameters:
        passportID - The unique identifier for the passport that was created.
        namespaceID - The unique identifier for the namespace into which the user has logged on.
        userID - The username of the user who logged on.
        theBiBusHeader - The biBusHeader that contains the information used to authenticate the user. Note that consumed form fields and credentials will not be part of that request.

      • logoff

        void logoff(java.lang.String passportID,
            java.lang.String namespaceID,
            java.lang.String userID,
            IBiBusHeader theBiBusHeader)
        Invoked when a logoff was issued from the user and is called before the passport is destroyed. A logoff cannot fail and there will be one logoff for each namespace that a user has authenticated to.
        Parameters:
        passportID - The unique identifier for the passport that will be destroyed.
        namespaceID - The unique identifier for the namespace into which the user has logged on.
        userID - The username of the user who logged on.
        theBiBusHeader - The biBusHeader that contains the information used to authenticate the user. The biBusHeader can be modified to remove existing cookies, form fields, and so on.

      • logonExpired

        void logonExpired(java.lang.String passportID,
                  java.lang.String namespaceID,
                  java.lang.String userID,
                  IBiBusHeader theBiBusHeader)
        Invoked when a passport has expired and is called right before the passport is destroyed. A logonExpired cannot fail and there will be one logonExpired for each namespace that a user has authenticated to.
        Parameters:
        passportID - The unique identifier for the passport that will be destroyed.
        namespaceID - The unique identifier for the namespace into which the user has logged on.
        userID - The username of the user who logged on.
        theBiBusHeader - The biBusHeader that contains the information used to authenticate the user. The biBusHeader can be modified to remove existing cookies, form fields, and so on.
